8. Technical/administrative protection measures for personal information
When processing users' personal information, the company is taking the following measures to ensure safety and prevent personal information from being lost, stolen, leaked, altered or damaged.
One-way encryption of passwords
“Company” does not collect passwords of platform members in partnership with service providers.
Preparation measures against hacking, etc.
	In order to prevent users' personal information from being leaked due to hacking, etc., we install and operate devices that block intrusion from the outside to prevent attacks and hacking from outside. In particular, servers containing users' personal information are connected to external Internet lines. We maintain the highest level of security by managing it separately rather than directly connecting it.
	In addition, we have a system to back up systems and data in case of an emergency, and we are taking measures to prevent damage caused by computer viruses by using anti-virus programs. Antivirus programs are updated periodically, and if a virus suddenly appears, a vaccine is provided as soon as it is available to prevent personal information from being violated.
Restrictions and training of processing staff
	The “Company” limits access to users’ personal information to the minimum number of people (persons in charge who can handle personal information), provides a separate password for this purpose, updates it regularly, and provides regular training to the person in charge. We always emphasize compliance with the company's personal information processing policy.
Operation of a dedicated personal information protection organization
	The “Company” checks the implementation of the company’s personal information processing policy and whether the person in charge complies with it through an in-house personal information protection organization, etc., and strives to immediately correct and correct any problems that are discovered. However, the company is not responsible for any problems arising from leakage of personal information such as ID, password, resident registration number, etc. due to the user's carelessness or Internet problems.
Access rights and log record retention
	Access rights are periodically reviewed and log records are stored safely.
